        ## Powerful

        Ceylon probably has one of the most **powerful type system** letting you
        express much more things than Java: **Union types**, intercection types, 
        high order functions. And Ceylon remains **fully interoperable** with Java.
  #bubble
    .bubble-block-transparent.fixed-vertical-bubble
      :markdown
        ## Readable

        Code is read much more often than written.  
        Ceylon focuses on readability
        via its extremely **regular syntax**, support for **treelike structures**, 
        explicit keywords and more.
  #bubble
    .bubble-block-transparent.fixed-vertical-bubble
      :markdown
        ## Predictable

        Ceylon is **unambiguous**, use a regular syntax,
        uniform rules, limits polluting choices and enforces **safety** at the 
        type system and compiler level. The type system prevents any
        **NullPointerException** and ClassCastException for example.
