        ## a Platform

        Ceylon is not only a language but a whole platform bringing a **modern SDK**.
        Ceylon runs on multiple backends: the **JVM** and **JavaScript** bringing the gap
        between clients and servers.
  #bubble
    .bubble-block-transparent.fixed-vertical-bubble
      :markdown
        ## Modularity

        Modularity is built at the core of the **language, SDK and tooling**.
        Ceylon compiles **modules** which are be published a **next-generation
        repository** called [Ceylon Herd](http://modules.ceylon-lang.org)
        bringing **social** to the community.
  #bubble
    .bubble-block-transparent.fixed-vertical-bubble
      :markdown
        ## Tooling

        Ceylon has been designed with **toolability** in mind. It comes with a 
        fully-fledged **Eclipse based [IDE](/documentation/current/ide/)**, **compiler**,
        debugger and documentation tool. Ceylon will come with a **build system**
        natively understanding modularity.
